 To add your name to the top of a LaTeX document, you have several options depending on how you want it to appear. Here are the most common approaches:

### 1. Using the title page elements

```latex
\documentclass{article}

\title{Your Document Title}
\author{Your Name}
\date{\today}

\begin{document}
\maketitle

% Rest of your document...
\end{document}
```

This creates a formal title page with your name as the author.

### 2. For a simple header without a full title page

```latex
\documentclass{article}

\begin{document}
\noindent\textbf{Your Name} \hfill \today

\vspace{1cm}

% Rest of your document...
\end{document}
```

### 3. Using fancyhdr package for a header on every page

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{fancyhdr}

\pagestyle{fancy}
\fancyhf{}
\rhead{\today}
\lhead{Your Name}
\cfoot{\thepage}

\begin{document}
% Your document content...
\end{document}
```

### 4. For academic papers with multiple authors

```latex
\documentclass{article}

\title{Your Paper Title}
\author{Your Name \\ \textit{Your Institution} \\ \texttt{your.email@example.com}}

\begin{document}
\maketitle

% Rest of your paper...
\end{document}
```

Choose the option that best fits your document's style and purpose. The first approach with `\author` is the most standard way in LaTeX documents.
